                ],
                "institute": "2GERGSI"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The UNILAC accelerator and the new",
                "recoil separator, Transactinide Separator and",
                "Chemistry Apparatus (TASCA)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For portions of the 259.4 MeV run and the entire",
                "254.6 MeV run, a 55 ug/cm2 thick carbon stripper foil",
                "was mounted directly upstream of the target to",
                "increase the charge state of the beam. For the",
                "231.2 MeV irradiation, targets with average thicknesses",
                "of 558-ug/cm2 206PbS, 522-ug/cm2 207PbS and 531-ug/cm2",
                "208PbS were used. All PbS targets were covered with",
                "10-ug/cm2 C-nat. 244PuO(2) targets with isotopic",
                "composition: 97.9% 244Pu, 1.3% 242Pu, 0.7% 240Pu, and",
                "less than 0.1% other were used. The 244PuO(2) targets",
                "were prepared on 2.22+-0.05 um thick Ti foils by",
                "electrochemical deposition from isobutanolic",
                "solution. Over the course of the experiment, four",
                "244Pu target segments with a beam dose weighted",
                "average target thickness of 438-ug/cm2 244Pu as",
                "495-ug/cm2 244PuO(2) were irradiated with typical beam",
                "intensities of 2.E+12 particles 1/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
